{
  "stem": "18770.3",
  "chunk_idx": 11,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 11.0,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 26,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "So it never-- you know, what is it?",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 26,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "You never leave home, you never go away.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 26,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "It never goes away.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 26,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "So that stays underneath.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 27,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "On, on the top layer, yes, very assimilated.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 27,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "Religious practice because of my mother.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 27,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "As long as my mother is alive, go to temple on Yom Kippur and go on Rosh Hashanah.",
      "word_count": 18
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 27,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "And there's a-- and there's Passover and, you know, and a few other things.",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 27,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "But my religious, formal religious thing, ends when my father dies.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 27,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "That is to say I go to temple every day to say Kaddish for him for a whole year, twice a day.",
      "word_count": 22
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 27,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "It's quite an experience when you're 15 and 1/2.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 27,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "But after that's over, without my father there as the sort of parental figure who would be making that go on longer, I basically-- you know, I do-- I stop going to-- I don't want go to shul on Saturdays anymore.",
      "word_count": 41
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 27,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "That all ends.",
      "word_count": 3
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 27,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 9,
      "text": "I don't keep a kosher home when I get married.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 27,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 10,
      "text": "So yeah, that, that's the way it shifts away.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 27,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 11,
      "text": "I mean, you know, it stays there, but the main dominant way that I live would be New York artist intellectual.",
      "word_count": 21
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 28,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "I think those things are very hard to tell exactly give proper weight to, you know, as what did what.",
      "word_count": 20
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 28,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "I think in my particular case-- because I think I was very emotionally sensitive to the dislocation of the war, probably a lot of it having to do with that loss of my governess at a critical time.",
      "word_count": 38
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 28,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "My sister was four years old, and for her, the loss of the governess, which she didn't have that strong bond that I did anyway, was not as traumatic it was for me.",
      "word_count": 33
    }
  ],
